'''Oscar Efrén Reyes''' (June 13, 1896, [[Baños de Agua Santa|Baños]] – December 6, 1966, [[Quito]]), was a historian, journalist, politician, researcher and an [[Ecuadorians|Ecuadorian]] teacher. He is remembered for his teachings as well as his historic research of Ecuador and America.{{clarify|date=February 2017}}

==Early life and education==
Reyes was born in [[Baños de Agua Santa|Baños]], [[Tungurahua Province]] on June 13, 1896, the only child of María Petronila Reyes Noboa.<ref name="la-hora-oscar-efren-reyes">{{cite news |date=12 August 2008 |title=Oscar Efrén Reyes |url=http://lahora.com.ec/index.php/noticias/show/758692/-1/Oscar_Efr%C3%A9n_Reyes.html |language=Spanish |newspaper=La Hora Nacional |location= |access-date=14 February 2017}}</ref><ref name="aviles-pino-encyclopedia-oscar-efren-reyes">{{cite web |url=http://www.enciclopediadelecuador.com/personajes-historicos/prof-oscar-efren-reyes/ |title=Prof. Oscar Efrén Reyes |last=Avilés Pino |first=Efrén |website=Enciclopedia del Ecuador |language=Spanish |access-date= 14 February 2017}}</ref><ref name="perez-pimentel-encyclopedia-oscar-efren-reyes">{{cite web |url=http://www.diccionariobiograficoecuador.com/tomos/tomo19/r4.htm |title=OSCAR EFREN REYES |last=Pérez Pimentel |first=Rodolfo |website=Diccionario Bibliografico del Ecuador |language=Spanish |access-date= 14 February 2017}}</ref> His father was a ''[[arriero]]'' (muleteer).<ref name="perez-pimentel-encyclopedia-oscar-efren-reyes" /> His grandparents, Francisco Reyes Hidalgo and Regina Noboa, owned a farm called ''La Escudilla''.<ref name="la-hora-oscar-efren-reyes" /><ref name="perez-pimentel-encyclopedia-oscar-efren-reyes" /> <!-- Due to his mother's difficult economic situation both she and Reyes would suffer from lack of food. [Should this be removed as promotional/unnecessary?] --> I<ref name="la-hora-oscar-efren-reyes" /> After the death of his mother in 1909 due to cancer,<ref name="perez-pimentel-encyclopedia-oscar-efren-reyes" /> he was placed in the care of his aunt and uncle, Rosita Romo de Reyes and Juan Reyes Noboa.<ref name="la-hora-oscar-efren-reyes" />

Eventually he received education in grammar and mathematics, paid for by Dominican parish priest Fray Juan Halflants, who had admired the literary knowledge of Reyes at the age of 15.<ref name="perez-pimentel-encyclopedia-oscar-efren-reyes" /> After two years of instruction and study, and under the watch of Halflants, the young 16 year old Reyes started his work as a teacher of children in the city of Baños, who still remember him for his introversion and kindness.<ref name="perez-pimentel-encyclopedia-oscar-efren-reyes" /><!-- This part seems promotional/unnecessary. It can be sourced to Pérez Pimentel's publication, but it would need to be reworded -->

In 1914, with a scholarship from the State,<ref name="perez-pimentel-encyclopedia-oscar-efren-reyes" /> Reyes enrolled at the Juan Montalvo Normal<!-- normal is a school for upcoming teachers -->.<ref name="aviles-pino-encyclopedia-oscar-efren-reyes" /> He graduated in 1916 with the highest honors.<ref name="la-hora-oscar-efren-reyes" /><ref name="perez-pimentel-encyclopedia-oscar-efren-reyes" />

==Death==
Reyes died in the city of [[Quito]] in the early morning of December 1, 1966,<ref name="la-hora-oscar-efren-reyes" /><ref name="aviles-pino-encyclopedia-oscar-efren-reyes" /><ref name="perez-pimentel-encyclopedia-oscar-efren-reyes" /> at a Military Hospital<!--literally "military hospital" in Spanish, and not the name of the hospital -->.<ref name="perez-pimentel-encyclopedia-oscar-efren-reyes" /> His remains were moved to Baños, his birthplace, on June 13, 1985.

